👉 Method overloading in JAVA

Two or more methods can have same name but different parameters .Such methods are called Overloaded Methods

void foo()
void foo(int a)    -------------> Overloaded Function foo
void foo(int a, int b)

Method Overloading cannot be performed by changing the return type of methods.

Example : 

public class Methods{
    static void sum(int a, int b){
        int sum = a+b;
        System.out.println("Sum : "+sum);
    }
    static void sum(float a, float b){
        float sum = a+b;
        System.out.println("Sum : "+sum);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        int a = 34;
        int b = 45;
        float c = 32.56f;
        float d = 34.56f;
        sum(a,b);
        sum(c,d);
    }
}

--> Here two methods having same name sum but different parameters int and float ... here sum is the method overloaded.

